PixelDiet reuses and adapts the WeChat-Moments-style "gear" image
compression strategy originated in Luban and carried into AdvancedLuban.
The following significant changes have been made relative to AdvancedLuban:

  - Reimplemented in Kotlin with a coroutines core and a Java-friendly
    callback API; the RxJava2 dependency has been removed.
  - Added content:// Uri and InputStream input sources for Android 10+
    scoped storage compatibility.
  - Switched to androidx.exifinterface for orientation handling.
  - Added WebP (lossy/lossless) output and API-aware encoding/decoding.
  - The library ships no native (.so) code by design.

